WEBVTT

00:00.420 --> 00:02.830
♪♪

00:03.380 --> 00:05.330
Previously on Andi Mack...

00:05.330 --> 00:06.830
I made something for you.

00:06.830 --> 00:10.210
Walker...I...
can't accept them.

00:10.210 --> 00:12.080
I have a boyfriend.

00:12.080 --> 00:14.040
Whoever he is, he's a lucky guy.

00:14.040 --> 00:16.290
Andi, I'm going to camp.

00:16.290 --> 00:17.290
For eight weeks.

00:17.290 --> 00:19.460
-I'm sorry.
-He'll be back
before you know it.

00:19.460 --> 00:21.790
You could say the same thing
about you and pops.

00:21.790 --> 00:23.960
Andi:
We have the ring!

00:23.960 --> 00:25.620
We're proposing tonight.

00:25.620 --> 00:26.580
We need a plan.

00:26.580 --> 00:27.750
Andi:
How about a cake?

00:27.750 --> 00:29.380
Bex:
Where do we put the ring?

00:29.380 --> 00:31.210
Andi:
Inside the cake!

00:31.210 --> 00:32.960
I've got a little surprise.

00:32.960 --> 00:35.210
The Renaissance Boys!

00:35.210 --> 00:36.920
Your boys need you.

00:36.920 --> 00:38.420
We got our first
international tour.

00:38.420 --> 00:39.960
For real?!

00:39.960 --> 00:42.670
Would you do us
the honor of becoming
our rhythm guitarist?

00:42.670 --> 00:44.080
What...?

00:44.080 --> 00:45.460
Let me help you with that!

00:45.460 --> 00:46.790
Here...

00:46.790 --> 00:48.750
what is this?

00:48.750 --> 00:50.330
Somebody tell me something.

00:50.330 --> 00:51.580
Um...

00:51.580 --> 00:52.880
Um...

00:52.880 --> 00:54.080
Bowie:
Um...?

00:56.210 --> 00:57.620
♪ ♪

01:04.330 --> 01:05.290
(sighs)

01:13.580 --> 01:15.620
This is the best day
of my life.

01:15.620 --> 01:17.330
Mine, too.

01:31.380 --> 01:33.960
Oh, I'm gonna cry.

01:33.960 --> 01:35.500
No, you're not.

02:03.080 --> 02:05.040
(sighs)
This is it.

02:09.750 --> 02:11.500
(eerie music)

02:11.500 --> 02:13.170
Ahh!

02:14.290 --> 02:15.420
Ahh!

02:18.330 --> 02:19.960
Ahh! (echoing) No!

02:21.290 --> 02:24.420
♪ I'm standin'
on the edge ♪

02:24.420 --> 02:29.330
♪ And everything I know-oh-oh
is blown away ♪

02:30.620 --> 02:33.670
♪ Life is upside down ♪

02:33.670 --> 02:38.290
♪ But any way it goes
I'll work it out ♪

02:40.170 --> 02:43.540
♪ Oh oh oh oh oh ♪

02:43.540 --> 02:47.330
♪ Here we go ♪

02:47.330 --> 02:50.170
-♪ One, two, three ♪
-♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪

02:50.170 --> 02:52.540
♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪

02:52.540 --> 02:54.880
♪ There ain't a map to follow ♪

02:54.880 --> 02:57.420
♪ But I'm with you all the way ♪

02:57.420 --> 02:59.710
♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪

02:59.710 --> 03:02.000
-♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪
-♪ Hey ♪

03:02.000 --> 03:04.290
♪ There ain't a map to follow ♪

03:04.290 --> 03:07.540
-♪ But I'm with you
all the way ♪
-♪ Hey ♪

03:07.540 --> 03:09.960
♪ All the way ♪

03:09.960 --> 03:11.960
That's so creepy!

03:11.960 --> 03:15.170
I know! And it was
a beautiful wedding.

03:15.170 --> 03:19.500
The dresses! My dream-brain
is an amazing stylist.

03:19.500 --> 03:21.580
You'll have time
to think about that.

03:21.580 --> 03:23.250
Bowie's still on tour
for a while, right?

03:23.250 --> 03:24.750
Four more months.

03:24.750 --> 03:27.540
But Jonah gets back
from Ultimate camp today.

03:27.540 --> 03:28.960
You heard from him?

03:28.960 --> 03:31.620
He sent me this text
the night before he left,
with the date,

03:31.620 --> 03:33.580
and "See you then!
Put it in your calendar!"

03:33.580 --> 03:36.250
Which I did, with an alert--

03:36.250 --> 03:37.880
I used that Drake song.

03:37.880 --> 03:40.000
The one where he's in the box?

03:40.000 --> 03:41.380
Yeah.

03:41.380 --> 03:43.960
I didn't miss him as much
as I thought I would.

03:43.960 --> 03:46.000
Or... at all.

03:46.000 --> 03:48.670
Oh, look who's all
"me, myself and I."

03:48.670 --> 03:50.620
It's nice.

03:50.620 --> 03:53.500
Not having to decide
who I am or...

03:53.500 --> 03:55.040
what I should call myself.

03:55.040 --> 03:57.790
You mean,
"boyfriend, girlfriend."

03:57.790 --> 04:00.330
The only time those words
ever really mattered to me

04:00.330 --> 04:02.250
was when I thought
I couldn't have them.

04:02.250 --> 04:04.750
It sounds like...
you've moved on.

04:04.750 --> 04:06.250
I think I have.

04:06.250 --> 04:09.710
It's one thing to say it to you
now, but when it's D-Day--

04:09.710 --> 04:11.620
-D-Day?
-Dimples.

04:13.830 --> 04:15.580
Oh, there's Cyrus.

04:18.500 --> 04:20.420
-He's wearing an ascot.
-Yeah.

04:20.420 --> 04:22.120
(in a bad British accent)
'Ello, poppets!

04:22.120 --> 04:24.710
(under her breath)
Oh, dear.

04:24.710 --> 04:28.540
Well, I guess we don't have
to ask how you enjoyed
your visit to London.

04:28.540 --> 04:30.880
(same bad British accent)
It was ah-mazin'!

04:30.880 --> 04:33.620
I may'av become
a bit of an Anglophile.

04:36.580 --> 04:38.580
-Thoughts?
-Ignore, and hope it goes away?

04:38.580 --> 04:40.750
That's asking a lot.

04:40.750 --> 04:41.920
Okay.

04:42.880 --> 04:44.580
-Ready to shop?
-Always!

04:44.580 --> 04:46.080
Tickety-boo!

04:46.080 --> 04:48.000
Okay...

04:48.000 --> 04:49.750
♪ ♪

04:59.210 --> 05:00.540
Ready?

05:06.960 --> 05:10.080
I just want to sit here all day
and look at myself.

05:15.210 --> 05:17.420
Is this your Before?

05:17.420 --> 05:18.750
I wouldn't know
it's the same person!

05:18.750 --> 05:22.290
Sh! I'm so sorry.
We're still learning manners.

05:22.290 --> 05:24.210
Look! This is incredible!

05:24.210 --> 05:26.880
We should make this her top
"Before and After."

05:26.880 --> 05:28.710
You're going to put my photos
up there?!

05:28.710 --> 05:30.710
Oh, no,
not if you don't want us to.

05:30.710 --> 05:34.540
But, you'd be an inspiration
to so many people.

05:34.540 --> 05:36.710
Umm... no.

05:39.540 --> 05:42.210
She should be more grateful!
You gave her a new life!

05:42.210 --> 05:45.750
Well, Mom, it's my job.

05:45.750 --> 05:46.960
It's what I do.

05:46.960 --> 05:49.670
-I want one.
-You want one, what?

05:49.670 --> 05:51.080
A new life.

05:51.080 --> 05:53.380
-You don't need a new life.
-Yes, I do!

05:53.380 --> 05:56.120
This is the past!
This is blahhh!

05:56.120 --> 05:59.000
Get rid of it!
Show me the future.

05:59.000 --> 06:01.000
(laughs)
What's gotten into you?

06:01.000 --> 06:04.750
Your father is out there,
somewhere, living his best life.

06:04.750 --> 06:07.000
I'm entitled to the same thing,
aren't I?

06:07.000 --> 06:09.290
Yes, you are.

06:09.290 --> 06:11.380
Do I have any more
appointments today?

06:11.380 --> 06:12.830
That was your last one.

06:12.830 --> 06:14.210
♪ ♪

06:17.750 --> 06:20.040
Let's do this.

06:20.040 --> 06:21.790
We'll need a Before picture.

06:25.460 --> 06:26.790
Have a seat.

06:26.790 --> 06:29.120
♪ ♪

06:29.120 --> 06:32.420
♪ You can be anyone at all ♪

06:32.420 --> 06:33.750
(bad British accent)
'Scuse me, Miss,

06:33.750 --> 06:35.580
could I trouble you for
a tad more salad cream?

06:37.210 --> 06:38.710
Ranch.

06:40.920 --> 06:43.170
I wish there was a ranch
we could send him to.

06:43.170 --> 06:44.830
Cyrus:
Oi, speak up, luv.

06:44.830 --> 06:45.880
Couldn't quite catch that.

06:45.880 --> 06:48.290
Stop talking
with an English accent.

06:48.290 --> 06:50.620
Y'know, it doesn't even feel
like an accent anymore.

06:50.620 --> 06:51.830
I think it's my true voice.

06:51.830 --> 06:53.750
-(Buffy laughs)
-(door chimes)

06:53.750 --> 06:55.380
Oh, no.

06:55.380 --> 06:58.170
-(door closes)
-Look what the cat dragged in.

06:58.170 --> 06:59.330
Is it Jonah?

07:01.080 --> 07:05.040
Ugggh. I am not ready
to have this conversation
in front of everyone.

07:05.040 --> 07:06.540
Guvnah!

07:06.540 --> 07:07.830
Breathe, breathe.

07:07.830 --> 07:09.080
Hey.

07:09.080 --> 07:11.040
Walker:
Hey.

07:12.750 --> 07:13.790
Walker?

07:13.790 --> 07:16.290
Hey, Andi.
Okay if I join you?

07:16.290 --> 07:19.960
Oh. I don't want to be rude,
but now isn't really
a good time.

07:19.960 --> 07:23.080
Andi, relax. I'm not here
to see you.

07:24.580 --> 07:25.790
Oh?

07:25.790 --> 07:27.750
He's here to see me.

07:29.920 --> 07:31.000
Ohhh.

07:34.540 --> 07:35.670
Are you mad?

07:35.670 --> 07:38.750
Well, I wouldn't describe myself
as overjoyed.

07:38.750 --> 07:40.920
(scoffs)
Why didn't you tell me
he was coming?

07:40.920 --> 07:42.500
I didn't know.

07:42.500 --> 07:45.620
-He does love
a surprise drop-in.
-Apparently.

07:45.620 --> 07:47.420
Well, you seem happy.

07:47.420 --> 07:49.830
(mumbling)

07:49.830 --> 07:51.710
Mm...

07:51.710 --> 07:54.920
-Yeah...
-(both laugh)

07:54.920 --> 07:57.080
So, I guess there's some stuff
you haven't told me.

07:57.080 --> 08:00.920
Not really. I mean,
there's been some texts...

08:00.920 --> 08:03.920
and... two VideoTimes.

08:03.920 --> 08:07.290
But I told him I couldn't
see him in person
until you knew about it.

08:07.290 --> 08:09.620
Well, now I know about it.

08:09.620 --> 08:10.920
Are you feeling weird
about this?

08:10.920 --> 08:12.120
No!

08:12.120 --> 08:14.920
Even a little bit?
Come on, you can tell me.

08:14.920 --> 08:16.830
I'm really not.

08:16.830 --> 08:19.500
I mean... Walker and me--
nothing ever really happened.

08:19.500 --> 08:20.880
He drew that picture of me,

08:20.880 --> 08:22.880
and we went out
that one time. That's it.

08:22.880 --> 08:27.250
We painted that mural,
and he gave me sneakers.

08:27.250 --> 08:30.000
I think that's it.
Look, this is silly.

08:30.000 --> 08:33.080
I'm making a scene,
and I barely know him.

08:33.080 --> 08:35.420
You're happy
and I'm happy for you.

08:35.420 --> 08:37.040
We should get back
to the table.

08:37.040 --> 08:38.290
You sure?

08:38.290 --> 08:41.170
Yeah! I just needed a minute
to wrap my mind around it,

08:41.170 --> 08:43.710
and... done.

08:43.710 --> 08:45.330
(both laugh)

08:48.830 --> 08:50.710
♪ ♪

08:54.620 --> 08:56.380
How are we?

08:56.380 --> 08:57.580
We're good.

08:58.620 --> 09:00.380
(bad British accent)
Lovely!

09:00.380 --> 09:04.040
This isn't bugging you?
That British accent?

09:04.040 --> 09:06.580
'Cause it's driving us crazy!

09:06.580 --> 09:08.580
I'm not one to pick sides.

09:08.580 --> 09:11.080
I'm new here,
I'm just trying to fit in.

09:18.920 --> 09:21.330
Well! This has been fun!

09:21.330 --> 09:24.000
-Andi...
-I'm... gonna go now.

09:24.000 --> 09:25.330
(laughs nervously)

09:25.330 --> 09:27.710
♪ ♪

09:27.710 --> 09:28.960
(door chimes)

09:33.710 --> 09:37.000
Well, that salad cream
certainly is taking
its sweet time, innit?

09:39.710 --> 09:42.920
It's like... it's-- it's like...
it's like --

09:42.920 --> 09:44.250
Bex:
Just spit it out.

09:44.250 --> 09:49.290
I'm-- I'm -- I'm trying.
It's like...it's like my mind
is like... aggh!

09:49.290 --> 09:51.620
Jonah...

09:51.620 --> 09:54.540
or Walker! It's like, I just--

09:54.540 --> 09:56.540
Stop beating yourself
up about this!

09:56.540 --> 09:58.880
And me.
You're a teenager.

09:58.880 --> 10:01.170
You won't be fully rational
for at least five years.

10:01.170 --> 10:03.880
If you don't want to help me,
just say you don't want
to help me.

10:03.880 --> 10:05.290
It's scientific fact.

10:05.290 --> 10:07.670
Your brain
isn't fully formed yet.

10:07.670 --> 10:09.920
-Look it up!
-You're being so mean.

10:09.920 --> 10:12.580
Celia:
She's being kind.
It's more like ten years.

10:12.580 --> 10:15.580
CeCe? Why didn't you
tell me she was in there?

10:15.580 --> 10:17.880
Because I thought she
would be out by now!

10:17.880 --> 10:19.540
Celia:
I'm not ready!

10:19.540 --> 10:22.540
-I'm still zhuzhing.
-Stop! You're going to zhuzh
yourself down to a little nub.

10:22.540 --> 10:25.000
-(doorbell rings)
-Could you get that?

10:25.000 --> 10:27.210
-Could you?
-Well, I'm busy.

10:27.210 --> 10:29.790
-It might be Jonah.
-I doubt it's Jonah.

10:29.790 --> 10:32.460
-It feels like it is!
-Why don't you want
to see Jonah?

10:32.460 --> 10:35.120
-Because...it's-- it's like--
-Forget I asked.

10:35.120 --> 10:36.830
Celia:
Is someone getting the door?

10:38.380 --> 10:39.710
Yes.

10:40.880 --> 10:42.960
-(doorbell rings again)
-Nevermind!

10:42.960 --> 10:46.040
-I have to get
this over with!
-Okay.

10:46.040 --> 10:48.500
Breathe.
(exhales loudly)

10:52.120 --> 10:54.540
-Hey, schnoo.
-Pops?!

10:54.540 --> 10:56.670
-Pops!
-(Ham chuckles)

10:56.670 --> 10:58.170
Ho, ho, ho!

10:59.210 --> 11:01.120
-It's Pops!
-I lost my keys.

11:01.120 --> 11:03.120
I think I dropped them
in the Ganges River.

11:03.120 --> 11:04.620
This thing has no pockets.

11:04.620 --> 11:06.290
-(both chuckle)
-Bex: Dad!

11:06.290 --> 11:07.540
Hey!

11:07.540 --> 11:09.960
Oh, oh, oh!

11:11.960 --> 11:13.460
Is your mom home?

11:13.460 --> 11:15.290
I hope she's happy to see me.

11:15.290 --> 11:16.830
(scoffs)
Oh, she will be!

11:18.170 --> 11:21.210
CeCe! Did you hear me?
Pops is home!

11:21.210 --> 11:23.500
I probably should
have changed.

11:23.500 --> 11:26.210
Oh... yeah, probably.

11:26.210 --> 11:27.670
She won't care.

11:27.670 --> 11:28.790
♪ ♪

11:33.880 --> 11:35.000
Ham?

11:35.000 --> 11:36.960
Celia.

11:36.960 --> 11:39.250
(gasp)
CeCe!

11:44.080 --> 11:46.210
Bex gave me a makeover.

11:46.210 --> 11:47.750
Do I look foolish?

11:47.750 --> 11:51.960
-Are you joking?!
You look sensational.
-No, not at all.

11:53.540 --> 11:55.710
I won't ask you
the same question.

11:55.710 --> 11:57.580
I think I know what you'd say.

12:00.750 --> 12:04.170
I'd say, "Welcome home."

12:04.170 --> 12:06.880
I'm so happy to be here.

12:06.880 --> 12:08.210
♪ ♪

12:11.920 --> 12:14.120
(both mumbling)

12:14.120 --> 12:16.080
Yeah, I should shower.

12:16.080 --> 12:18.080
Uh... is my soap still here?

12:18.080 --> 12:20.120
Everything is right
where you left it.

12:20.120 --> 12:22.620
Soap, I'm comin' to get ya!

12:22.620 --> 12:24.790
(Ham laughs)

12:25.710 --> 12:27.080
(giggles)

12:30.460 --> 12:33.120
-He looks good.
-He looks happy.

12:33.120 --> 12:34.960
He looks like a yeti.

12:36.290 --> 12:39.040
Don't give me that!
We were all thinking it.

12:43.210 --> 12:45.000
Still nothing?

12:45.000 --> 12:47.170
She said she was
cool with it, but...

12:47.170 --> 12:49.210
maybe she's really not.

12:49.210 --> 12:51.040
Maybe she just needs
a little more time.

12:51.040 --> 12:53.540
Exactly.
"Keep calm
and carry on."

12:53.540 --> 12:55.540
That's what my people
always say.

12:55.540 --> 12:57.040
We're your people.

12:57.040 --> 12:59.580
But we won't be if you
keep talking that way.

12:59.580 --> 13:02.250
Calm down, luv,
you sound like the business end
of a tea kettle.

13:04.540 --> 13:06.500
Do you want him to stop?
I can get him to stop.

13:08.210 --> 13:10.120
-Don't hurt him.
-I'll be gentle.

13:11.670 --> 13:14.000
(very strong Cockney accent)
Oi! Mate!
I'm tote'ly wiv yer, yeah?

13:14.000 --> 13:16.290
-What?
-You see, I'd rabbit
and pork like this

13:16.290 --> 13:18.210
aw the beastly
nickel and dime,

13:18.210 --> 13:19.670
but nobody'd
know wot I'm on about!

13:19.670 --> 13:21.960
You're me bright boy!

13:21.960 --> 13:24.040
Right cop to know
each uvver,
wotcha say?

13:25.080 --> 13:26.830
(normal voice)
You're right.
This is annoying.

13:26.830 --> 13:29.250
-(laughs)
-I can make myself useful.

13:29.250 --> 13:30.580
So I see.

13:30.580 --> 13:33.120
Did I tell you guys,
next year I'm going to Spain?

13:33.120 --> 13:35.120
(with a Spanish accent)
To run with the bulls!

13:35.120 --> 13:36.120
(Spanish music riff)

13:36.120 --> 13:37.670
That sounds safe.

13:39.210 --> 13:42.210
-Bex: No!
-Please! You did it for CeCe.

13:42.210 --> 13:44.960
Well, you're perfect
exactly the way you are.

13:44.960 --> 13:46.170
Aww.

13:46.170 --> 13:47.580
I'm not saying it to be nice.

13:47.580 --> 13:50.540
Well, I'm saying it
to be nice. My point is,

13:50.540 --> 13:54.000
is that there is absolutely
no way to improve
upon this.

13:54.000 --> 13:55.880
So, I'm not
giving you a makeover.

13:55.880 --> 14:00.580
Ugh. It's like living with
a fairy godmother that won't
bippity-bop me.

14:03.210 --> 14:05.420
How about a red carpet look?

14:05.420 --> 14:08.170
♪ ♪

14:08.170 --> 14:09.620
That I can do.

14:09.620 --> 14:13.330
♪ Every day I find
another piece ♪

14:13.330 --> 14:16.460
♪ Of another world
I've never seen ♪

14:16.460 --> 14:18.500
♪ Picking up and
chasing dreams ♪

14:18.500 --> 14:22.330
♪ That won't let go of me ♪

14:22.330 --> 14:24.170
♪ And I-I-I ♪

14:24.170 --> 14:27.750
♪ Was never meant
for the faint-hearted ♪

14:27.750 --> 14:30.330
♪ I-I-I ♪

14:30.330 --> 14:31.420
Wow!

14:31.420 --> 14:35.960
Yes! Fabulous! Stunning!
To the camera!

14:35.960 --> 14:38.290
Andi Mack,
what is your latest project?

14:38.290 --> 14:41.580
Well, it's for science class,
and it's on the solar system.

14:41.580 --> 14:44.580
Amazing! You pick that dress
out yourself?

14:44.580 --> 14:46.580
-I did!
-Your style is exquisite!

14:46.580 --> 14:48.790
Buffy, Cyrus, collaborators.

14:48.790 --> 14:50.790
Did you choose them?
Or did they choose you?

14:50.790 --> 14:53.000
-It was very mutual.
-I knew it!

14:53.000 --> 14:54.330
Andi Mack! One more question!

14:54.330 --> 14:55.330
(knocking at door)

14:57.000 --> 14:58.330
(in unison)
Jonah.

15:00.000 --> 15:01.460
How do I look?

15:02.960 --> 15:05.460
Do you realize
this never happens?

15:05.460 --> 15:08.830
Nobody ever looks like that
when they run into a guy
from their past.

15:08.830 --> 15:10.830
They usually look like this.

15:10.830 --> 15:13.580
Oh, I can't wait to see his face
when you open the door!

15:13.580 --> 15:15.750
-Okay.
-Okay.

15:15.750 --> 15:17.540
Breathe, breathe.

15:17.540 --> 15:19.000
Just... answer the door.

15:19.000 --> 15:20.420
Right.

15:20.420 --> 15:21.540
Okay.

15:22.790 --> 15:23.960
Dad!

15:27.920 --> 15:29.210
Bowie?

15:33.120 --> 15:35.290
(all laugh, then groan)

15:35.290 --> 15:38.380
-(muttering over each other)
-Just set that down, yeah.

15:38.380 --> 15:40.830
-Try that again?
-Yeah.

15:40.830 --> 15:42.290
♪ ♪

15:45.420 --> 15:47.460
(sighs)

15:47.460 --> 15:48.790
I missed you.

15:54.290 --> 15:55.790
♪ ♪

15:55.790 --> 15:57.960
Andi:
I can't believe you're here!

15:57.960 --> 15:59.500
Did something happen?

15:59.500 --> 16:02.790
Because according to your
schedule, which I have
right here,

16:02.790 --> 16:08.420
you're supposed to be on stage
in Tokyo in 20 minutes.

16:08.420 --> 16:10.960
Something did happen...

16:10.960 --> 16:13.210
about two months ago,

16:13.210 --> 16:15.210
when I found a ring
inside a cake.

16:17.620 --> 16:20.330
Hey, does this belong to anyone
or can I call finders keepers?

16:24.460 --> 16:26.830
I guess I have to be
the adult here.

16:26.830 --> 16:31.380
Solid plan, especially
because you are the adult here.

16:33.880 --> 16:35.880
We were going to propose.

16:35.880 --> 16:38.290
Together. It was my idea.

16:38.290 --> 16:42.170
The cake was also my idea.
The whole dinner was actually
my idea.

16:42.170 --> 16:44.830
Hey! Who came up
with the proposing? Me.

16:44.830 --> 16:47.380
Who found the ring? Me.

16:47.380 --> 16:49.380
Okay, uh, when's
the actual proposal?

16:49.380 --> 16:51.830
Spoiler alert--
my answer's yes.

16:55.290 --> 16:57.290
We're not proposing.

16:58.460 --> 17:01.500
Hold up.
Was that definitely decided?

17:01.500 --> 17:03.330
You're not?

17:03.330 --> 17:07.120
-Plus, he already said yes!
-No, the Renaissance Boys
already proposed.

17:07.120 --> 17:08.380
They were ahead of us.

17:08.380 --> 17:11.040
-I can tell them no.
-No, you cannot tell them no!

17:11.040 --> 17:12.790
You have to go on that tour!

17:16.830 --> 17:18.420
Then what happens to this?

17:19.540 --> 17:21.500
I'll hang on to it.

17:21.500 --> 17:24.460
And then, six months from now,
when you get back,

17:24.460 --> 17:26.540
we'll pick up
where we left off.

17:26.540 --> 17:28.580
Does that work for you?

17:28.580 --> 17:30.460
No.

17:30.460 --> 17:34.420
It sounds like another
messed-up marriage proposal.
I don't get it!

17:34.420 --> 17:37.460
It's such a simple concept,
with a very basic procedure,

17:37.460 --> 17:40.460
and for some reason,
you two just cannot
make it happen!

17:40.460 --> 17:43.080
♪ ♪

17:43.080 --> 17:45.290
I'm sorry.

17:46.960 --> 17:48.540
I shouldn't have said that.

17:50.170 --> 17:52.380
We love each other,

17:52.380 --> 17:54.540
that's what matters.

17:55.960 --> 17:58.500
That's all that matters.

17:59.710 --> 18:01.960
Who cares if we don't
get this part right?

18:05.210 --> 18:06.920
I remember that.

18:07.960 --> 18:10.380
You left out the part
where you're four months early.

18:10.380 --> 18:12.380
Something intervened.

18:12.380 --> 18:14.960
Let me guess. The Universe!

18:14.960 --> 18:19.620
Close! The Universe...
ity of Michigan.

18:19.620 --> 18:21.670
Micah, our drummer,
got into law school!

18:21.670 --> 18:26.120
-Oh, that's great!, but--
-You just canceled
the rest of the tour?

18:26.120 --> 18:29.040
Also, Rafe threw his back out
and Guthrie met a girl
in Australia,

18:29.040 --> 18:31.790
and plus, I never really
wanted to go in the first place.

18:31.790 --> 18:35.290
Well, that doesn't answer
all my questions.

18:35.290 --> 18:36.880
I still have
a lot of questions.

18:36.880 --> 18:38.960
Well, I just have one.

18:41.170 --> 18:43.500
Actually, so do I.

18:45.000 --> 18:46.920
(Andi gasps)

18:54.330 --> 18:55.880
(in unison)
Will you marry me?

18:55.880 --> 18:57.000
Yes!

18:57.000 --> 19:00.540
Oh, sorry! Sorry, uh,
keep going.

19:00.540 --> 19:02.420
(chuckles)

19:04.380 --> 19:05.670
(in unison)
Yes!

19:07.670 --> 19:11.080
-(in unison)
Nailed it!
-Finally!

19:19.080 --> 19:21.960
Oh! We need pictures!
Where is the camera?!

19:21.960 --> 19:24.500
And bubbles! Bubbles!

19:27.580 --> 19:29.170
(knocking at door)

19:29.170 --> 19:30.330
(groans)

19:35.960 --> 19:39.580
-Yo!
-Yo! What?!

19:39.580 --> 19:41.960
-Bex: Jonah!
-Hey, Bex!

19:41.960 --> 19:44.040
-Andi!
-What?

19:44.040 --> 19:46.500
Someone here to see you!

19:46.500 --> 19:48.420
(Dan Gautreau & Wolfgang Black -
"Friday Night Forever")

19:52.710 --> 19:54.500
Andi:
Jonah! Hey!

19:54.500 --> 19:55.710
Hi!

19:55.710 --> 19:58.250
-My parents are getting married.
-Cool!

19:58.250 --> 20:01.750
♪ Oh my brain, on Sunday ♪

20:01.750 --> 20:04.460
♪ The weekend seems
so far away ♪

20:04.460 --> 20:06.920
♪ It's all work and no play ♪

20:06.920 --> 20:10.170
♪ Forever planning our escape ♪

20:10.170 --> 20:12.460
♪ Ooo-oo-oo-oo-oo-oo ♪

20:14.580 --> 20:17.710
-Oh, it's good to see you!
-Sorry I didn't come sooner.

20:17.710 --> 20:19.710
Oh, don't apologize,
that's totally okay.

20:22.960 --> 20:27.120
So you and me, we're...?

20:27.120 --> 20:28.500
Definitely.

20:28.500 --> 20:31.580
-Just friends.
-Still together.

20:34.920 --> 20:36.250
Next on Andi Mack:

20:36.250 --> 20:38.290
I told Jonah that I just
want to be friends.

20:38.290 --> 20:40.460
But he still thinks
we're a couple.

20:40.460 --> 20:43.170
Either way, I should probably
invite him to
the Moon Festival Party.

20:43.170 --> 20:46.380
-You've outdone yourself!
-Andi: It's beyond
Chinese New Year.

20:46.380 --> 20:48.710
Please tell me this doesn't mean
what I think it means.

20:48.710 --> 20:50.120
She invited Aunt May.

20:50.120 --> 20:52.880
Isn't it wonderful?
Mothers and daughters together.

20:52.880 --> 20:55.710
-Bonding.
-It's so stressful!

20:55.710 --> 20:57.880
Jonah:
Saying the right things,
wearing the right clothes!

20:57.880 --> 20:59.750
I don't know what we're gonna do
about this mess.

20:59.750 --> 21:02.080
If I were you,
I'd break up with me.

21:02.080 --> 21:03.670
Do you want to break up with me?
